EVO HTML to PDF Converter general package works well both in 32-bit and 64-bit environments. The 64-bit environments offers more memory for the executing processes. This version of the package is optimized to take advantage of this opportunity when converting very large HTML documents.

This package is not compatible with 32-bit environments. For 32-bit environments please use the general version of the package.

EVO HTML to PDF Converter is a .NET library that can be easily integrated in any type of .NET applications to convert web pages, HTML strings and streams to PDF or to image. The converter has support for HTML5, CSS3, SVG, Canvas, Web Fonts and JavaScript. Does not require installation or any third party tools.

EVO HTML to PDF Converter for .NET Product offers full support for HTML tags, CSS styles, SVG vector graphics, Canvas, Web Fonts, JavaScript, page breaks control with CSS styles, repeating HTML table header and footer in PDF pages, live URLs and internal links in PDF, automatically generated bookmarks, HTML in the headers and footers, PDF merge, PDF split and PDF edit.
summary: Convert HTML to PDF in your .NET applications using the EVO HTML to PDF Converter.

This package is purely a library of useful classes which contains useful Selenium Webdriver related methods of interacting with web browsers when automating web applications. As this library was written strictly for interview DEMOs, it has been developed to intentionally cover automating ONLY within; Google Chrome and Firefox browsers, as well as, limite web elements types. However, the library can, quite easily be extended to cover additional web browsers of your choice {e.g. IE, PhantomJS etc} as well as other generic web element types in HTML. The library also contains other useful classes that can be used to efficiently automate the web application under test}. All Selenium related methods for automating generic browser actions can be accessed via the abstract class: SeleniumBase. Enjoy.
summary: This package is purely a library of useful classes which contain Selenium Webdriver related methods of interacting with web browsers {covers only Chrome and Firefox browsers at the moment}
